🔥 MODULE 1 — Instant Wins (Your First 30 Minutes)
Goal: Get 3 "holy sh*t" moments before lunch and hook yourself on the value.
Lesson 1.1 — Summarize 200 Emails in 10 Seconds
🎣 Hook: The Monday morning inbox problem is dead.
🎯 Scenario: You're back from vacation with 247 unread emails; do this instead of 4 hours of triage.
🎬 Demo Script:
	Open Outlook and click the Copilot panel.
	Paste the following prompt:
📋 Copy-Paste Prompt: "For all emails received in the past 7 days (sent + received), summarize the key points, identify action items that need MY response, and prioritize them highest-to-lowest. For each item include: one-line summary, who's waiting, and urgency (🔴 today / 🟡 this week / 🟢 FYI)."
	Review output and click items to jump to emails.
	Bonus: "Draft replies for items 1–5 in my writing style."
🔁 Recap: Achieve inbox zero in 15 minutes.
________________________________________
Lesson 1.2 — Never Take Meeting Notes Again
🎣 Hook: The Facilitator Agent replaces your note-taker and action-item tracker.
🎯 Scenario: Focus 100% on a 30-minute Teams meeting while getting perfect notes.
🎬 Demo Script:
	In the Teams invite, go to More options (...) → Copilot and other AI.
	Toggle Record and transcribe automatically to ON.
	Toggle Facilitator Agent to ON and click Apply.
	After the meeting, open the Recap tab for summaries, action items, and transcripts.
⚡ Bonus: After the meeting, Copilot also generates a video highlight reel — a narrated summary you can share with anyone who missed the call.
🔁 Recap: Focus on people, not typing.
________________________________________
Lesson 1.3 — Generate a Full Report in 60 Seconds
🎣 Hook: Deliver an executive-grade, cited report before your coffee cools.
🎯 Scenario: A last-minute request for a "quick market analysis" due by 9 AM.
🎬 Demo Script:
	In Copilot, go to Tools → Researcher.
	Paste:
📋 Copy-Paste Prompt: "Create an executive research report on [TOPIC]. Include: Executive summary, 3 biggest trends, 2 risks/opportunities, next actions, and cite every claim."
	Review citations and click Edit in Pages to export to Word.
⚡ Pro Tip: For deeper analysis, switch to Think Deeper mode before running the Researcher prompt. It takes 30 seconds longer but produces significantly better citations and reasoning.
🔁 Recap: Use Researcher the moment anyone says "look into...".
