⚡ MODULE 3 — Agents That Replace Work
Goal: Stop prompting and start delegating; agents finish jobs, not just chats.
Lesson 3.1 — Agent Mode: Let Copilot Actually Do the Work
🎣 Hook: You've been asking Copilot to help. Agent Mode lets it do.
🎯 Scenario: You have a rough 3-page Word doc that needs to become a polished executive brief — restructured, tightened, formatted — in 5 minutes.
🎬 Demo Script:
	Open your document in Word and click the Copilot icon.
	Toggle Agent Mode ON (top of the Copilot pane).
	Paste this prompt:
📋 Copy-Paste Prompt: "Restructure this document into an executive brief: add an executive summary at the top, tighten every paragraph to 2–3 sentences max, fix formatting inconsistencies, and add section headers. Keep my data and conclusions — just make it boardroom-ready."
	Watch Copilot make changes live in the document — not in a chat bubble.
	Review the tracked changes and accept or reject each one.
⚡ Pro Tip: Agent Mode also works in Excel (clean data, build charts) and PowerPoint (redesign slides, fix layouts). Same toggle, same power.
🔁 Recap: Chat suggests. Agent Mode executes. Turn it on for any task that involves more than one step.
________________________________________
Lesson 3.2 — Prompt Coach
🎣 Hook: Bad prompts equal bad outputs; use Prompt Coach to get clear.
🎬 Demo Script:
	Go to Tools → Prompt Coach.
	Answer its questions on Goal, Context, Source, and Expectations.
Part	Ask Yourself
Goal	What exactly do I want?
Context	Who's it for? What's the background?
Source	What files/data should it use?
Expectations	Length, tone, format?
⚡ Pro Tip: Once you nail a prompt, click the Save to Prompt Gallery icon. Name it, tag it, and share it with your team. Build a library so nobody starts from scratch.
________________________________________
Lesson 3.3 — Build Your Personal Copilot
🎣 Hook: Teach Copilot who you are once to stop repeating yourself forever.
🎬 Demo Script:
	In Settings → Personalization → Custom Instructions, define your role, preferred format (e.g., Executive summary), and tone.
	Add key projects to Saved Memories.
