Lesson 4.3 — Copilot Pages: Your Team's Shared Brain
🎣 Hook: Every great Copilot output dies in your chat history. Pages keeps it alive.
🎯 Scenario: You just generated a project status summary in Copilot. Your manager and two teammates need to see it, edit it, and add their sections — without you copy-pasting into an email.
🎬 Demo Script:
	After any Copilot response, click Edit in Pages.
	Your output opens in a collaborative canvas — like a living document.
	Click Share and add your teammates.
	Everyone can edit, add prompts, and refine — together, in real time.
📋 Copy-Paste Prompt (to kick it off): "Create a weekly project status page with three sections: What's done, What's in progress, and What's blocked. Pull from my emails and Teams chats from the past 5 days."
⚡ Pro Tip: Pages persist. Bookmark your most-used ones. Use them as living dashboards instead of static reports nobody updates.
🔁 Recap: Chat is for you. Pages is for your team. If the output matters to more than one person, put it in a Page.
